{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-challenges-classic-show-tsx","path":"/learn/project-euler/project-euler-problems-1-to-100/problem-70-totient-permutation","result":{"data":{"challengeNode":{"challenge":{"block":"project-euler-problems-1-to-100","demoType":null,"title":"Vežba 70: Permutacija totijenta","description":"<section id=\"description\">\n<p>Ojlerova Totijent funkcija, ${\\phi}(n)$ (ponekad nazvana phi funkcija), koristi se za određivanje broja pozitivnih brojeva manjih ili jednakih <code>n</code> koji su uzajamno prosti sa <code>n</code>. Na primer, pošto su 1, 2, 4, 5, 7 i 8 svi manji od devet i uzajamno prosti sa devet, ${\\phi}(9) = 6$. Broj 1 se smatra uzajamno prostim sa svakim pozitivnim brojem, pa je ${\\phi}(1) = 1$.</p>\n<p>Zanimljivo je da je ${\\phi}(87109) = 79180$, i da je 79180 permutacija broja 87109.</p>\n<p>Pronađi vrednost <code>n</code>, 1 &#x3C; <code>n</code> &#x3C; <code>limit</code>, koja ${\\phi}(n)$ je permutacija <code>n</code> i odnos $\\displaystyle\\frac{n}{{\\phi}(n)}$ postižu najniži nivo.</p>\n</section>","id":"5900f3b21000cf542c50fec5","hasEditableBoundaries":false,"instructions":"","notes":null,"challengeType":1,"helpCategory":"Euler","videoUrl":null,"superBlock":"project-euler","translationPending":false,"forumTopicId":302183,"hooks":null,"fields":{"slug":"/learn/project-euler/project-euler-problems-1-to-100/problem-70-totient-permutation"},"required":[],"usesMultifileEditor":false,"challengeFiles":[{"fileKey":"scriptjs","ext":"js","name":"script","contents":"function totientPermutation(limit) {\n\n  return true;\n}\n\ntotientPermutation(10000);","head":null,"tail":null,"editableRegionBoundaries":[],"history":["script.js"]}],"saveSubmissionToDB":null,"tests":[{"text":"<p><code>totientPermutation(10000)</code> Trebalo bi da vrati broj.</p>","testString":"assert(typeof totientPermutation(10000) === 'number');"},{"text":"<p><code>totientPermutation(10000)</code> treba da vrati <code>4435</code>.</p>","testString":"assert.strictEqual(totientPermutation(10000), 4435);"},{"text":"<p><code>totientPermutation(100000)</code> treba da vrati <code>75841</code>.</p>","testString":"assert.strictEqual(totientPermutation(100000), 75841);"},{"text":"<p><code>totientPermutation(500000)</code> trebalo bi da vrati <code>474883</code>.</p>","testString":"assert.strictEqual(totientPermutation(500000), 474883);"},{"text":"<p><code>totientPermutation(10000000)</code> trebalo bi da vrati <code>8319823</code>.</p>","testString":"assert.strictEqual(totientPermutation(10000000), 8319823);"}]}}},"pageContext":{"challengeMeta":{"blockHashSlug":"/learn/project-euler/#project-euler-problems-1-to-100","dashedName":"problem-70-totient-permutation","certification":"project-euler","disableLoopProtectTests":true,"disableLoopProtectPreview":false,"superBlock":"project-euler","chapter":null,"module":null,"block":"project-euler-problems-1-to-100","isFirstStep":false,"template":null,"required":[],"isLastChallengeInBlock":false,"nextChallengePath":"/learn/project-euler/project-euler-problems-1-to-100/problem-71-ordered-fractions","prevChallengePath":"/learn/project-euler/project-euler-problems-1-to-100/problem-69-totient-maximum","id":"5900f3b21000cf542c50fec5","saveSubmissionToDB":null},"projectPreview":{"challengeData":{"challengeType":1,"challengeFiles":[{"name":"script","ext":"js","contents":"function arrangedProbability(limit) {\n  // Based on https://www.mathblog.dk/project-euler-100-blue-discs-two-blue/\n  let blue = 15;\n  let discs = 21;\n\n  while (discs < limit) {\n    const nextBlue = 3 * blue + 2 * discs - 2;\n    const nextDiscs = 4 * blue + 3 * discs - 3;\n\n    blue = nextBlue;\n    discs = nextDiscs;\n  }\n  return blue;\n}","history":["script.js"],"fileKey":"scriptjs"}]}},"id":"/learn/project-euler/project-euler-problems-1-to-100/problem-70-totient-permutation"}},"staticQueryHashes":["3858520367"],"slicesMap":{}}